    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-28T15:18:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-28T15:18:00-05:00" n="635"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/5–2854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d635fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MLT1"
                            >Merchant</persName> of <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-28T16:18:00-04:00"
                            >May 28, 1954—4:18 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 137. Eyes only for the Under Secretary
                    from the Secretary. It seems to me that there is a growing possibility that the
                    DVR cease fire proposal might develop into form of <hi rend="italic">de
                        facto</hi> partition which <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> might
                    be expected to encourage and which French might find impossible to refuse but
                    which Associated States would oppose.</p>
                <p>If this situation should arise we would face necessity for very difficult
                    decision and I hope it would be possible for you to inform me before taking
                    irrevocable position so that I could consult with the President. This would of
                    course have bearing on paragraph 5 of your President-approved instructions
                        (<gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 138).<note n="2" xml:id="d635fn2"
                        >Dated May 12, <ref target="#pg_778">p. 778</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
